cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.PF 

This paper deals with the improvement of TCP traffic over IEEE 802.11ac, which is a wireless networking standard. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of aggregation and ARQ protocols, which are related to information theory and communication systems, making cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) likely categories as well. The paper also proposes a new model for transmission, which involves system-level design and optimization, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the improvement of TCP Goodput, which is a performance metric, making cs.PF (Performance) a possible category as well.
